1
00:01:31,770 --> 00:01:34,979
[Wind Direction]

2
00:01:35,479 --> 00:01:37,940
[Episode 24]

3
00:01:43,420 --> 00:01:43,990
Dad.

4
00:01:44,470 --> 00:01:45,940
Didn't you quit smoking?

5
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:48,229
Why are you smoking again?

6
00:01:48,490 --> 00:01:49,210
Quit it.

7
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:51,920
When your mom is home, she controls me.

8
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:54,200
When she's not, you do.

9
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,670
I don't even have any freedom

10
00:01:55,670 --> 00:01:57,460
now that I'm old.

11
00:01:57,970 --> 00:01:59,690
Who has freedom these days?

12
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:01,420
Alright, you are free enough,

13
00:02:01,810 --> 00:02:03,610
with no family to worry about.

14
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:05,230
I think being single

15
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:06,510
is quite good for him.

16
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,389
Marriage or not,

17
00:02:08,419 --> 00:02:09,370
it's not that important.

18
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:10,889
If you find the wrong mate,

19
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:13,030
you'll never feel comfortable

20
00:02:13,070 --> 00:02:14,670
in the lifetime.

21
00:02:17,110 --> 00:02:18,790
You're implying something.

22
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:19,950
Did you wake up too fast this morning

23
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:20,990
and let out what's been on your mind,

24
00:02:20,990 --> 00:02:21,550
right?

25
00:02:22,010 --> 00:02:22,740
Wait, Dad.

26
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:25,630
My mom always said if you can live together, fine,

27
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:27,270
but if not, just get a divorce.

28
00:02:27,270 --> 00:02:29,310
Are you two really

29
00:02:29,329 --> 00:02:30,730
going through a crisis?

30
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:34,370
Pengfei,

31
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,120
the day after I married your mom,

32
00:02:37,150 --> 00:02:38,540
she told me,

33
00:02:38,540 --> 00:02:39,870
"If we can live together, fine;

34
00:02:39,870 --> 00:02:41,400
if not, just get a divorce."

35
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:43,350
How many years have passed?

36
00:02:43,350 --> 00:02:44,750
It's been decades.

37
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:47,530
Are we getting a divorce? She was just bragging.

38
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:48,770
Dad, tell me the truth.

39
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:50,270
Have you ever thought about it?

40
00:02:50,270 --> 00:02:50,829
No.

41
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:52,680
It's just the three of us at home today.

42
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,890
Say whatever you want,

43
00:02:53,890 --> 00:02:55,090
we won't betray you.

44
00:02:55,370 --> 00:02:56,520
The three of us must be united,

45
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,120
right?

46
00:02:59,660 --> 00:03:01,700
If you say I never had those thoughts,

47
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,100
that's just nonsense.

48
00:03:04,170 --> 00:03:06,000
But I don't believe it.

49
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:07,620
Which family

50
00:03:08,010 --> 00:03:10,400
has lived together for decades

51
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:13,190
without any grievances

52
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:14,660
or dissatisfaction?

53
00:03:16,260 --> 00:03:16,860
Yes.

54
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,630
No matter how much

55
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:20,310
love there is,

56
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:22,670
it can't stand up to the everyday trifles.

57
00:03:24,530 --> 00:03:27,130
When Baoshan was born,

58
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:30,200
the family's food supply was tight.

59
00:03:30,540 --> 00:03:32,140
I'd get up early in the morning

60
00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:33,930
to work

61
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,030
and wouldn't come back until it was dark.

62
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:38,440
I couldn't see the sun all day.

63
00:03:40,670 --> 00:03:42,030
You know

64
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:43,040
your mother's temper.

65
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,940
She spoke harshly

66
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,540
and was very vain,

67
00:03:47,570 --> 00:03:48,980
always bragging.

68
00:03:49,350 --> 00:03:50,500
It made me so angry

69
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:52,010
that my chest hurt.

70
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:54,860
My coronary heart disease today

71
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:56,990
is caused by the anger I felt back then.

72
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:58,280
Dad,

73
00:03:58,829 --> 00:04:00,310
did you

74
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:01,820
run away from home once?

75
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:05,930
I stayed at the drilling team

76
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,420
for more than half a month.

77
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:08,830
At the time, I thought

78
00:04:08,910 --> 00:04:09,690
the worst would be getting divorced.

79
00:04:09,690 --> 00:04:10,770
I'm not afraid.

80
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:12,310
Wait. Why?

81
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:15,990
Back then...

82
00:04:17,790 --> 00:04:19,560
Because I bought cigarettes

83
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,070
or

84
00:04:22,840 --> 00:04:24,840
borrowed money? No.

85
00:04:27,450 --> 00:04:29,370
I can't remember

86
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:31,400
why

87
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:32,930
it got to that point.

88
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,850
I have a realization.

89
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:40,840
It got so bad

90
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:42,550
that I even ran away from home,

91
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:44,190
but I can't remember

92
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:45,510
why it happened

93
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:46,870
when you asked.

94
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,290
What does this mean?

95
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:51,360
-It means...
-It means you have a poor memory.

96
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,260
Bullshit!

97
00:04:55,460 --> 00:04:57,480
It means I can't live without your mother,

98
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,320
our family,

99
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:02,180
and you two siblings.

100
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:07,120
We used to argue and fight when we were young,

101
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:10,100
and now I really can't remember the details.

102
00:05:10,860 --> 00:05:12,300
At my age,

103
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,600
what I can remember...

104
00:05:15,870 --> 00:05:17,530
I remember you and your sister

105
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:19,530
learning to speak when you were little,

106
00:05:19,530 --> 00:05:22,130
and the first time you called me "Dad."

107
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:27,010
I remember being wronged,

108
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,560
and your mom

109
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:31,700
went to the factory to confront others on my behalf.

110
00:05:32,350 --> 00:05:33,920
What I remember most clearly

111
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,490
is the night

112
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:38,159
we got married;

113
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:40,630
I whispered to your mom.

114
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:42,740
What did you say?

115
00:05:43,070 --> 00:05:44,420
I told her that

116
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:46,560
I would die after her,

117
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,000
and I couldn't bear to

118
00:05:49,030 --> 00:05:51,610
let her alone.

119
00:05:52,070 --> 00:05:53,390
You're quite nasty.

120
00:05:53,730 --> 00:05:55,060
Were you cursing my mom?

121
00:05:55,550 --> 00:05:56,120
You...

122
00:05:58,110 --> 00:05:59,990
Enough. Let's drink.

123
00:06:00,370 --> 00:06:01,850
It's almost cold. Here.

124
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:03,150
Pengfei, let me do it.

125
00:06:03,150 --> 00:06:03,740
Okay.

126
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:04,750
Here.

127
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:05,750
Okay.

128
00:06:07,940 --> 00:06:08,790
-Come on.
-Come on. Dad.

129
00:06:08,790 --> 00:06:09,430
Here, Dad.

130
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,360
Life is a long road

131
00:06:12,490 --> 00:06:14,330
with many obstacles.

132
00:06:14,930 --> 00:06:15,770
We've passed

133
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,920
all those obstacles.

134
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:19,580
[Free]

135
00:06:19,970 --> 00:06:22,600
[Life is a long road.]

136
00:06:25,770 --> 00:06:29,350
[Linqi Oilfield No. 2 High School]

137
00:06:30,930 --> 00:06:33,090
Why was my essay returned?

138
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,110
You wrote a gongfu story

139
00:06:35,110 --> 00:06:36,390
for the essay contest.

140
00:06:36,390 --> 00:06:37,630
Of course it was returned.

141
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:38,630
There's no restriction on the theme.

142
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:40,030
Why can't I wrote a a gongfu story?

143
00:06:40,030 --> 00:06:41,830
Of course not.

144
00:06:41,990 --> 00:06:43,710
Did you think you submit to a TV station?

145
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:45,909
It's only natural for it to be returned.

146
00:06:45,909 --> 00:06:47,190
But it was really unfair

147
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:48,710
that mine got returned.

148
00:06:49,010 --> 00:06:51,120
Your essay was filled with praise for your dad;

149
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:53,120
even the teacher couldn't stand it.

150
00:06:53,470 --> 00:06:55,060
That was my genuine feeling.

151
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:57,230
That was just because you lacked pocket money.

152
00:06:57,230 --> 00:06:58,040
Latest news.

153
00:06:58,060 --> 00:06:58,980
Latest news.

154
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:02,340
The first-place winner of this essay contest

155
00:07:02,340 --> 00:07:05,340
will go on to compete in the provincial essay contest.

156
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,730
Who won the first prize?

157
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:10,250
I don't know. It's not you anyway.

158
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,260
Why are you so close to him?

159
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,480
I'm just gossiping.

160
00:07:19,340 --> 00:07:22,270
Watching the sailboats from the Yellow Crane Tower.

161
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:29,790
Just do your work;

162
00:07:29,810 --> 00:07:30,920
why did you kick it?

163
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:32,730
Don't ruin my books.

164
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:35,430
It's such a waste that you get to read the books.

165
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:37,310
Look, everyone is working hard

166
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:38,370
in their own positions

167
00:07:38,370 --> 00:07:39,690
at this precious time.

168
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,470
But only you

169
00:07:40,470 --> 00:07:42,730
are idle and have accomplished nothing.

170
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:43,159
Where's your dignity?

171
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,030
Aren't you at least a little ashamed

172
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:44,830
or something?

173
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:46,180
A man

174
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,830
can't rely solely on a handsome face;

175
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:49,070
he needs to have knowledge,

176
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:49,830
and ideas.

177
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:51,230
And also knowing to work.

178
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:52,350
Go.

179
00:07:52,370 --> 00:07:53,240
Move those few pots of withered flowers

180
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:53,840
over here.

181
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,880
I'm not just sitting here,

182
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:02,790
you know,

183
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,850
I've been thinking about working.

184
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:06,010
Let me tell you...

185
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:07,140
Tell me

186
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,560
when do you plan to leave?

187
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:09,590
Where should I go?

188
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:11,270
I'm working on

189
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:12,070
my grand plans

190
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,230
and, by the way, also figuring out

191
00:08:14,230 --> 00:08:15,360
my personal issues.

192
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:18,700
You mean you and Director Xiao?

193
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,430
Sister, well,

194
00:08:21,350 --> 00:08:22,520
you think about it seriously;

195
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:23,990
do you think Director Xiao and I

196
00:08:23,990 --> 00:08:24,920
are a good match?

197
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,020
No.

198
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:28,270
Do you also think

199
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:29,600
Director Xiao is a bit

200
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:30,610
too...

201
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,799
Too excellent.

202
00:08:33,539 --> 00:08:34,870
What kind of man are you?

203
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,280
How can you compare

204
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,679
to her?

205
00:08:38,470 --> 00:08:39,429
She is

206
00:08:39,429 --> 00:08:40,740
the director of Teaching and Discipline at Linqi No. 2 High School,

207
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,990
wielding great influence.

208
00:08:41,990 --> 00:08:43,320
You're just an unemployed

209
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,210
drifter,

210
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:46,350
and just know eating and sleeping.

211
00:08:46,350 --> 00:08:46,910
Let me tell you,

212
00:08:46,910 --> 00:08:48,150
even if she gives you a glance,

213
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:49,630
it's because she's an intellectual

214
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:51,430
with a kind heart.

215
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:54,750
The way you look at things

216
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:55,790
is very strange.

217
00:08:56,570 --> 00:08:57,210
Anyway,

218
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,040
you're just a middle-aged woman

219
00:08:59,040 --> 00:08:59,870
with limited understanding,

220
00:08:59,870 --> 00:09:01,130
so it's not your fault.

221
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,820
A man should establish himself by 30.

222
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:05,260
You're over 30.

223
00:09:05,690 --> 00:09:06,660
That's not important.

224
00:09:06,660 --> 00:09:07,520
Let me tell you,

225
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:08,990
Mom is right.

226
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:10,720
I'm a late bloomer;

227
00:09:11,110 --> 00:09:12,970
I'll make achievements after 30.

228
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:15,130
I'll establish a career before starting a family.

229
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:16,210
Establish...

230
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:18,950
Let me see what you can establish.

231
00:09:19,390 --> 00:09:20,070
I really have an

232
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:20,870
immature idea.

233
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:21,930
Listen to me first.

234
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:24,440
You see, a man's career

235
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:25,860
generally falls into two categories:

236
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:27,390
employment

237
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:28,970
or entrepreneurship.

238
00:09:29,070 --> 00:09:29,830
I've been employed

239
00:09:29,830 --> 00:09:30,910
for so many years.

240
00:09:30,910 --> 00:09:32,350
I don't think it suits me.

241
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,270
But since I've had in-depth discussions

242
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:35,310
with Director Xiao,

243
00:09:35,310 --> 00:09:37,560
I feel there's a bit of a connection

244
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,380
between me and the education sector.

245
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:43,980
You... You're going to cause trouble for the school again.

246
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:45,190
Stop it!

247
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:45,990
The education sector

248
00:09:45,990 --> 00:09:46,790
doesn't just involve teaching;

249
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:48,120
there's also the canteen,

250
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:50,050
and I have an advantage in that area.

251
00:09:50,050 --> 00:09:50,990
Sister, think about it.

252
00:09:50,990 --> 00:09:51,750
If I really work

253
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:52,870
in their school,

254
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:53,590
it wouldn't just

255
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:54,730
be about me and Director Xiao;

256
00:09:54,730 --> 00:09:56,400
I could also support Miaomiao and Yaya.

257
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,570
That would be all harm and no benefits for our family...

258
00:09:58,570 --> 00:10:01,310
No, that would be all benefits and no harm for our family, right?

259
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:01,840
You...

260
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,760
Are you trying to pursue Director Xiao

261
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,590
or just looking for a job?

262
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:09,480
I want

263
00:10:10,570 --> 00:10:11,300
love

264
00:10:11,590 --> 00:10:12,520
and career both.

265
00:10:12,810 --> 00:10:14,410
I need to excel in both areas.

266
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:15,910
It's broken.

267
00:10:19,070 --> 00:10:19,710
You...

268
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:22,700
Class begins.

269
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:23,590
Stand up.

270
00:10:24,210 --> 00:10:27,410
Good afternoon, teacher.

271
00:10:28,150 --> 00:10:28,700
Sit.

272
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:31,670
Before class,

273
00:10:31,670 --> 00:10:33,390
I have good news to announce.

274
00:10:34,430 --> 00:10:35,500
Our classmate, Qiang Xiaowa,

275
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:37,130
won first place

276
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:38,080
in this essay contest

277
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:40,010
with the work "The Ideal Country."

278
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:44,000
Qiang Xiaowa

279
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,630
will go to Qingdao

280
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:47,040
to represent our Linqi No. 2 High School

281
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,170
in the provincial essay competition.

282
00:10:56,940 --> 00:10:58,740
Okay, let's start the class.

283
00:10:59,310 --> 00:11:00,270
Turn to page 68.

284
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:21,370
I knitted it myself.

285
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:28,720
This is so beautiful.

286
00:11:29,510 --> 00:11:31,070
I like this color.

287
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:33,850
Help me give it to Grandma.

288
00:11:37,410 --> 00:11:39,020
This is for Grandma?

289
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:42,830
She made vests

290
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:43,990
for me and Zi.

291
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:45,950
I don't even know

292
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:47,650
