00:11:49,930 --> 00:11:51,580
It might not be perfect,

295
00:11:51,730 --> 00:11:53,590
but it's the thought that counts.

296
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:56,580
Okay.

297
00:11:57,310 --> 00:11:59,170
I'll help you give it to her later.

298
00:12:19,350 --> 00:12:20,560
This is for you.

299
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,590
Inside

300
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:33,500
is the poem I wrote

301
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,780
for the essay contest.

302
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:37,510
Even though it didn't win any awards,

303
00:12:37,510 --> 00:12:39,110
I still want to give it to you.

304
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:45,030
Thank you.

305
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:56,270
When is the final?

306
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,560
During the May Day holiday.

307
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:01,420
Going to Qingdao during the May Day holiday?

308
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:02,350
I want to go too.

309
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:04,910
I don't want to go.

310
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:06,110
Why?

311
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,440
I don't have time.

312
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:13,520
You don't have time during the May Day holiday?

313
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:14,870
Xiaowa,

314
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:16,380
why?

315
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,600
Nothing.

316
00:13:19,180 --> 00:13:20,520
It's just an essay contest,

317
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,650
not very important.

318
00:13:22,390 --> 00:13:23,320
It is important.

319
00:13:23,350 --> 00:13:24,600
It's not your own business.

320
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,200
It's about our team.

321
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:27,750
We finally have a proper reason

322
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,760
to get out,

323
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:29,810
especially during the holiday.

324
00:13:29,810 --> 00:13:30,960
Let's go together.

325
00:13:31,430 --> 00:13:32,060
Right?

326
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,680
I have to ask my mom.

327
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:36,040
I have no freedom at all.

328
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:37,480
Right?

329
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:39,720
I'm fine with anything.

330
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:41,580
It's settled then.

331
00:13:41,710 --> 00:13:44,060
We're going to Qingdao during the May Day holiday.

332
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:46,030
To Qingdao!

333
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:47,920
Can I go?

334
00:13:47,950 --> 00:13:50,550
Just tell me.

335
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:51,820
Get up from the floor.

336
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,600
You're really...

337
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,690
Aren't you shamed to sit on the ground like that,

338
00:13:56,690 --> 00:13:58,050
especially as a girl?

339
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:00,230
Why are you always

340
00:14:00,230 --> 00:14:02,310
thinking about having fun all day long?

341
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:03,550
It's not just for fun.

342
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:05,200
I'm participating in the contest.

343
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,320
What contest?

344
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:07,130
Did you win any awards?

345
00:14:07,130 --> 00:14:08,490
What does it have to do with you?

346
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:10,620
It's our team's business.

347
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:12,640
Besides, it's the May Day holiday.

348
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:15,550
It's only three days. Why can't I go?

349
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:17,560
Go.

350
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:18,670
Go ask your dad.

351
00:14:19,910 --> 00:14:20,790
I don't care.

352
00:14:25,210 --> 00:14:26,040
Dad.

353
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:28,690
You're finally back.

354
00:14:28,690 --> 00:14:29,890
Let me take it for you.

355
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:30,930
Let me take it.

356
00:14:30,930 --> 00:14:32,660
-What happened?
-Give it to me.

357
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:34,910
I want to go to Qingdao

358
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:36,830
with Li Si and Qiang Xiaowa

359
00:14:36,830 --> 00:14:37,950
during the May Day holiday.

360
00:14:37,950 --> 00:14:39,550
Qiang Xiaowa won the essay contest

361
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:41,210
and is moving on to the finals.

362
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:43,790
Li Si and I want to go with him. You know,

363
00:14:43,820 --> 00:14:45,130
it's such an important event,

364
00:14:45,130 --> 00:14:47,420
and we want to broaden our horizons

365
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:48,870
and see how large contests are run

366
00:14:48,870 --> 00:14:50,270
in the city.

367
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:51,310
Maybe we can even make some

368
00:14:51,310 --> 00:14:52,400
talented friends.

369
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:55,690
You just want to go to Qingdao for fun, don't you?

370
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:58,590
No, that's just secondary.

371
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:02,160
Dad, please.

372
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:04,430
Can you let me go?

373
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:06,570
Please.

374
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:07,530
Come.

375
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:09,850
You can go.

376
00:15:11,790 --> 00:15:13,580
Thank you, Dad. I Love you.

377
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:16,210
Aren't you going to take my bag inside?

378
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:19,510
What are you talking about?

379
00:15:19,510 --> 00:15:20,690
Did you even listen to what she said

380
00:15:20,690 --> 00:15:21,690
before agreeing?

381
00:15:23,470 --> 00:15:25,110
It's not a big deal.

382
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,540
It's the May Day holiday,

383
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:28,400
let the kids go have fun together.

384
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:29,630
Have you forgotten the last time they went to Hong Kong?

385
00:15:29,630 --> 00:15:30,660
If it hadn't been for the injury,

386
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:32,270
they might not have come back.

387
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:33,030
You see, last time,

388
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:34,030
it was because

389
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,720
we kept stopping them

390
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,610
that they almost got into trouble?

391
00:15:37,610 --> 00:15:38,590
They've grown up now,

392
00:15:38,590 --> 00:15:40,310
and they need to gain some experience.

393
00:15:40,310 --> 00:15:41,720
Besides, it's not far.

394
00:15:41,860 --> 00:15:43,590
If she can't figure out a short trip like this,

395
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:44,490
how will she handle

396
00:15:44,490 --> 00:15:45,630
the journey of life later on?

397
00:15:45,630 --> 00:15:47,150
You can't say anything

398
00:15:47,150 --> 00:15:48,830
without dragging it into a life lesson, can you?

399
00:15:48,830 --> 00:15:49,860
You're even turning this

400
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:50,740
into a life lesson for life.

401
00:15:50,740 --> 00:15:51,670
Have some water.

402
00:15:52,870 --> 00:15:54,200
Wasn't it your dad

403
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,730
who said life is a long road?

404
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:57,640
Yeah, life is a long road

405
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,030
with hurdles at every step.

406
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,620
Go cook.

407
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:04,800
Go cook!

408
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:13,350
With words of family love, my eyes fill with tears;

409
00:16:14,020 --> 00:16:18,100
years of separation weigh heavily on my heart.

410
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:22,740
My father has long since passed away,

411
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:27,550
and every festive season, my tears flow like a spring.

412
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,570
What does "passed away"

413
00:16:32,570 --> 00:16:33,380
mean?

414
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:35,560
You mean I'm dead?

415
00:16:35,950 --> 00:16:36,750
No.

416
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:39,390
I'm expressing longing.

417
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,850
But isn't it still about death?

418
00:16:43,850 --> 00:16:45,710
How can you miss me if I'm not dead?

419
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:50,010
Forget that part. Listen to the next one.

420
00:16:51,710 --> 00:16:53,950
In front of my father's tomb, the grass grows tall.

421
00:16:53,950 --> 00:16:54,510
Wait, Li Si.

422
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:55,730
What do you want?

423
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,550
Do you want me to die?

424
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,430
Are you playing some kind of truth game?

425
00:16:59,430 --> 00:17:00,780
What truth game?

426
00:17:00,810 --> 00:17:02,270
Do you think I'm unfilial?

427
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:05,280
It's just an artistic metaphor,

428
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:06,369
and an allusion to classical references.

429
00:17:06,369 --> 00:17:07,849
I didn't write the poem.

430
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:11,780
My essay for the contest

431
00:17:12,790 --> 00:17:14,250
is mainly about expressing

432
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:16,910
how fatherly love is as steadfast as a mountain.

433
00:17:18,329 --> 00:17:19,089
Dad!

434
00:17:19,630 --> 00:17:21,700
Fatherly love is as steadfast as a mountain?

435
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:23,630
Tell me, how much money do you want?

436
00:17:24,089 --> 00:17:25,220
I don't want money.

437
00:17:25,339 --> 00:17:26,579
This contest is free.

438
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:27,910
It's free?

439
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:30,540
I'm going to Qingdao.

440
00:17:30,540 --> 00:17:31,340
Qingdao?

441
00:17:33,090 --> 00:17:34,720
I'm going to Qingdao during the May Day holiday.

442
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,250
It won't interfere with school.

443
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:36,820
Just go.

444
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:39,590
Dad. Dad.

445
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:40,040
Well...

446
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:42,300
Participating in the contest in Qingdao

447
00:17:42,330 --> 00:17:43,340
is free,

448
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:44,520
but the travel to Qingdao

449
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,400
costs money.

450
00:17:46,150 --> 00:17:47,950
You still want money, do you?

451
00:17:49,390 --> 00:17:50,260
You've been reciting

452
00:17:50,260 --> 00:17:51,040
Tang and Song poetry here;

453
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:52,440
are you trying to make a profit?

454
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,080
Li Si,

455
00:17:54,210 --> 00:17:55,490
you can't even set a price for it.

456
00:17:55,490 --> 00:17:56,600
I can't set a price?

457
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,080
Wait, Dad.

458
00:17:58,110 --> 00:18:00,440
-Listen to the remaining part.
-Get lost!

459
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:02,550
Dad, you stay inside.

460
00:18:02,550 --> 00:18:04,150
I'll read it for you outside.

461
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:08,540
Lying peacefully in the tomb for 40 years,

462
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:14,190
with yearly offerings during the Lantern Festival and Tomb-Sweeping Day.

463
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:15,790
You little bastard!

464
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:17,180
What's Qingming?

465
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:20,620
Min?

466
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:21,550
Come in.

467
00:18:23,050 --> 00:18:23,950
I'm coming in.

468
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:27,760
What's wrong?

469
00:18:28,170 --> 00:18:28,690
Here.

470
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:30,740
Have some water.

471
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:32,880
Are you hungry?

472
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,810
What do you want for dinner?

473
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:38,760
I don't want to cook.

474
00:18:38,790 --> 00:18:40,360
Let's have tomato egg noodles.

475
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:41,570
Making it simple, okay?

476
00:18:41,570 --> 00:18:42,440
Okay.

477
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:44,470
Mom,

478
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:45,810
I have something

479
00:18:45,810 --> 00:18:47,040
to discuss with you.

480
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,360
-Well, I…
-Wait a minute.

481
00:18:56,950 --> 00:18:57,590
Hello?

482
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:01,990
Really?

483
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:05,540
Is she coming alone?

484
00:19:06,070 --> 00:19:07,270
Where is she staying?

485
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:10,880
Okay, I got it.

486
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:13,040
Bye.

487
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:15,240
Mom.

488
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:16,760
Who's coming?

489
00:19:17,110 --> 00:19:19,530
Yang said that Grandma is coming during the May Day holiday.

490
00:19:19,530 --> 00:19:21,260
She is going to live in our home.

491
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:24,030
Why is she coming?

492
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:27,950
She said her colleague's grandson is getting married.

493
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:29,640
She's coming for the wedding.

494
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:33,950
It's Grandma's first time

495
00:19:33,950 --> 00:19:34,820
visiting our home,

496
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:36,080
so you need to be on your best behavior.

497
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:36,920
Do you hear me?

498
00:19:37,370 --> 00:19:38,760
No matter how she treats us,

499
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,410
we must be polite to her.

500
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:41,630
Don't drop the ball.

501
00:19:41,650 --> 00:19:42,520
Do you hear me?

502
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:43,170
Yes.

503
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,280
Weren't you going to discuss something with me?

504
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:49,070
What is it?

505
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:50,160
Nothing.

506
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,580
I want to eat meat tonight.

507
00:19:53,580 --> 00:19:55,640
Tomato and egg noodles are too plain.

508
00:19:56,860 --> 00:19:57,700
Okay.

509
00:19:58,380 --> 00:19:59,910
I'll cook some meat for you.

510
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:01,060
Wait for me.

511
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:03,910
Have some water.

512
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:11,380
I want to go to Qingdao.

513
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:12,890
I also want to go.

514
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:18,160
The movies at the Cultural Palace

515
00:20:18,230 --> 00:20:19,710
aren't worth watching.

516
00:20:20,810 --> 00:20:22,340
Even if I want to go on a date,

517
00:20:22,630 --> 00:20:23,430
there's no decent place around

518
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:24,890
in our oilfield compound.

519
00:20:27,930 --> 00:20:29,660
Are you going to date with Fang?

520
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:31,280
Not exactly.

521
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,190
It's just that we've been getting along

522
00:20:33,190 --> 00:20:34,110
well recently,

523
00:20:34,130 --> 00:20:35,360
so I want to take things

524
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:36,550
a step further.

525
00:20:38,590 --> 00:20:40,210
I'm doing this for you and Miaomiao.

526
00:20:40,210 --> 00:20:40,890
No.

527
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:43,240
If you two end up together,

528
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,710
Fang would be my aunt.

529
00:20:45,510 --> 00:20:47,110
But if things don't work out,

530
00:20:48,110 --> 00:20:49,830
Cheng Miaomiao and I will have a tough time

531
00:20:49,830 --> 00:20:50,800
at school.

532
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:53,890
If I really take action,

533
00:20:54,010 --> 00:20:55,810
there's no way it won't work out.

534
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:57,310
I'm

535
00:20:57,330 --> 00:20:57,990
in the stage of

536
00:20:57,990 --> 00:20:59,790
moving forward right now.

537
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,890
But with the current limitations,

538
00:21:03,550 --> 00:21:05,080
it's hard to make progress.

539
00:21:06,610 --> 00:21:07,380
Uncle,

540
00:21:08,930 --> 00:21:10,170
I know a place that

541
00:21:10,210 --> 00:21:12,070
can help you make a breakthrough.

542
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:15,280
The green one next to it.

543
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:16,760
Here.

544
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:17,670
Thank you.

545
00:21:17,710 --> 00:21:18,840
You're welcome.

546
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:20,940
You've won first place,

547
00:21:20,940 --> 00:21:22,350
so why don't you want to go?

548
00:21:22,350 --> 00:21:23,820
They are willing to go with you.

549
00:21:23,820 --> 00:21:24,900
That's great.

550
00:21:26,470 --> 00:21:28,860
Even if I go, I might not win.

551
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:31,890
They are all students from big cities.

552
00:21:32,450 --> 00:21:34,180
They must write better than me.

553
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:35,910
Who cares if you win or not?

554
00:21:35,910 --> 00:21:36,410
Xiaowa,

555
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:37,900
you just go to broaden your horizons,

556
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:38,540
